\cf9 # Writer Spec \'97 Base Prose Template Family (Omega V4)\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 ## Version\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Spec Version: 1.0\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Status: Active\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Applies To: All base prose templates used in Omega / V4 book assembly\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 ---\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 ## 1. Purpose\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 This document defines the **writing contract** for a template family used in book assembly.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 The goal of this prose is not persuasion, motivation, or instruction alone.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 The goal is **regulation, clarity, and restored agency**.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 **Reader outcome (non-negotiable):**  \cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 After reading, the reader feels **seen**, **grounded**, and **able to take a small next step**.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 ---\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 ## 2. Voice & Tone\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 ### Voice\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Calm\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Grounded\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Confident without authority signaling\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Feels like a seasoned guide, not an expert performing\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 ### Tone\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Emotionally attuned\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Respectful of suffering\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Oriented toward agency, not dependency\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 ### Explicitly prohibited\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Hype or urgency\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Moral judgment\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Guru language\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Clinical detachment\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Sales or conversion framing\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 **Rule:**  \cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 The prose must feel safe to read late at night.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 ---\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 ## 3. Reader Relationship Model\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 The writer relates to the reader as:\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 - A witness who names what is already happening\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - A translator of internal experience\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - A guide who walks alongside\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 The writer is **not**:\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - A savior\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - A therapist\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - An influencer\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - An authority demanding belief\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 ---\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 ## 4. Prose Mechanics\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 ### Sentence level\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Average length: 10\'9618 words\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Mix of short grounding sentences and medium explanatory sentences\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - At most 1\'962 single-line emphasis sentences per section\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 ### Paragraph level\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - 2\'965 sentences per paragraph\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - White space is intentional\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - No dense blocks of text\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 ### Reading level\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Grade 8\'9610\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Emotionally adult, linguistically accessible\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 ---\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 ## 5. Content Invariants (Must Always Hold)\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 ### A. Validation before explanation\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 Pain is named and legitimized before any insight or reframe.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 ### B. Systems over personal failure\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 Suffering is framed as:\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - nervous system overload\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - cultural pressure\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - environmental mismatch\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 Never as:\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - weakness\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - lack of effort\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - incorrect belief\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 ### C. Agency is restored\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 The prose must:\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Offer permission\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Offer clarity\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Offer usable perspective\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 It must never imply dependence on the teacher, system, or content.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 ---\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 ## 6. Relationship to Teachers\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 Teachers are framed as:\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Observers\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Translators\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Lineage carriers\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Designers of practices\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 They are **not** framed as:\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Perfect beings\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Saviors\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Objects of devotion\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 The teaching always matters more than the teacher.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 ---\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 ## 7. Relationship to Ancient Wisdom\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 Ancient wisdom is framed as:\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Systems\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Maps\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Technologies refined over time\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 Avoid:\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Metaphysical claims without grounding\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Belief-based language\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Myth without function\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 Preferred framing:\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 > \'93This tradition discovered something practical about how humans work.\'94\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 ---\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 ## 8. Embodiment Requirement\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 Every template must include at least one embodied reference:\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - breath\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - posture\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - sensation\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - nervous system state\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - felt sense\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 Even if no formal exercise is included.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 ---\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 ## 9. Structural Compatibility\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 Templates must be safe to assemble with:\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - system_atoms\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - teacher_bank stories\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - exercises\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - locale overlays\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 Therefore:\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - No hard-coded names\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - No fixed cultural assumptions\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - No time-specific references\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 ---\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 ## 10. Exclusions\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 This template family is not used for:\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - News articles\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Sales pages\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Social media posts\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - Performance scripts\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 This prose is designed for **slow, reflective reading**.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 ---\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 ## 11. Acceptance Checklist\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 A template passes only if:\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - It feels calming when read aloud\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - It does not shame or pressure the reader\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - It never tells the reader what to believe\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - It respects the reader\'92s intelligence\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 - It can be reused thousands of times without fatigue\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 ---\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 ## 12. Internal Test\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 \'93If this paragraph were read to a stressed teenager at night, would it help them breathe a little easier?\'94\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 If not, it does not belong in this family.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
