\cf0 \cb2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf9 You might not have a clear name for what you\'92re feeling.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 It can show up as restlessness, heaviness, or a quiet sense that something is off.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 Not dramatic. Just persistent.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 If you\'92ve been pushing yourself to keep going while something inside feels tight or tired, there is a reason.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 And it isn\'92t because you are failing.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 When the nervous system is under constant demand, it adapts by bracing.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 That bracing can become so familiar that it fades into the background.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 You keep functioning, but something essential feels muted.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 Many people reach this point without realizing how much effort it has taken just to stay upright.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 The body learns to endure before the mind has words for it.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 If this sounds familiar, pause for a moment.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 Notice where your body is holding itself right now.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 No need to change anything.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 Just notice.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs32 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa80\partightenfactor0

