\f7\b\fs40 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs32 \cf0 Purpose:
\f0\b0 \uc0\u8232 Explain 
\f3\i why
\f0\i0  the struggle makes sense, in a grounded, non-clinical way.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f11\fs28 \cf0 \cb5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf9 What you are experiencing is not random.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 When the nervous system stays in a heightened state for too long, it begins to prioritize protection over presence.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 Attention narrows.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 Breath shortens.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 The body prepares for a threat that never quite resolves.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 This is not a flaw in your design.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 It is how human systems survive prolonged pressure.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 Modern life asks for constant output without consistent recovery.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 Over time, the system compensates by staying alert, even when rest is needed.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 The result can feel like disconnection, fatigue, or emotional flatness.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 Understanding this changes the story.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 Nothing is broken.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 The system is doing its best with the signals it has been given.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf9 \cb2 When pressure eases, even slightly, the system remembers how to settle.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 That capacity has not disappeared.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf9 \cb2 It has only been waiting for the right conditions.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs32 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f7\b\fs40 \cf0 Template 3 \'97 
